Just a warning. I'm not against this site or torrents in any way (fuck, no), but I had to warn whoever happens to try this movie (or any from hollywood). 

It finally happened. Charter/Disney emailed my dad with all the evidence that I'd downloaded "Tangled", though I forget which torrent I used (might've been this one; who knows?). In other words, Copyright Infringement (Damn it!). Luckily, it was just a warning this time (For fuck's sake, I fully intend to get the Blu-ray when it's released next month.), so I deleted the downloaded file, along with "Black Swan" (which was UNAVAILABLE where I am, except for 200+ miles out of the way. Quite imposible at that time.), and the "Avatar: Director's Cut", which I just recently ordered via Amazon.com.  

Anyway, hopefully I won't get warnings or worse, busted for those other two as I deleted the content, bought one (and maybe I'll purchase the other, too). Because frankly, I can't afford fines and I'd rather not have my ass thrown into jail. 

It seems the vultures are finding ways to go after users of The Pirate Bay now. Hopefully, they won't care about (some) software programs and lesser known films, anime and the like.
